http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Three-day-model-UN-conference-from-Thursday/article13994393.ece

The three-day International Model United Nations Conference organised by the School of Law, Christ University, will begin on Thursday. Over 350 students from Law schools and colleges in India, Malaysia, China, South Korea, Bangladesh and other countries will participate in the conference, which will have debates and discussion on international politics and issues.SpeakersSpeakers include Joanne Katz, Professor of Legal Studies, Missouri Western State University, Danish Sheikh, and David Tushaus. The agenda of the fourth edition of the conference includes the Syrian crisis, refugee treatment and capital punishment.